Step 1: Identify the relevant figures from the problem.
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -6,856,840.58
 • Net Profit = -2,035,736.52

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio using the formula:
 Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)

Step 3: Substitute the values:
 Ratio = (-6,856,840.58) / (-2,035,736.52)

Step 4: Since both values are negative, the negatives cancel out and the calculation becomes:
 Ratio ≈ 6,856,840.58 / 2,035,736.52 ≈ 3.37

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is approximately 3.37.
